.TH HSH 1 "11 August 2025" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
HSH \-  A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ ARGUMENTS ]
.br
.B hsh
.RB { \-h | \-\-help }
.br
.B hsh
.RB { \-V | \-\-version }

.SH DESCRIPTION
A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C.
It provides a basic environment to execute system commands, similar to the standard sh shell.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH EXAMPLES
In interactive mode:

.nf
./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($) exit

.fi

In non-interactive mode:

.nf
julien@ubuntu:/# echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2

julien@ubuntu:/# cat test_ls_2
/bin/ls
/bin/ls

julien@ubuntu:/# cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.fi


